Sentencas: Solution impregnated La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Ni0.2O3 + Gd-doped CeO2 (LSCN + GDC) cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC) are prepared and their electrochemical properties are evaluated and compared with the conventional LSCN cathodes.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical performance of solution impregnated La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Ni0.2O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The results indicate that the cathode performance can be enhanced by the presence of the nanosized microstructure produced with the solution impregnation method.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical performance of solution impregnated La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Ni0.2O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It is determined that the amount of LSCN loading in the LSCN + GDC composite cathode needs to be higher than 35 wt% in order to achieve a performance superior to that of the conventional LSCN cathode.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical performance of solution impregnated La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Ni0.2O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The optimum amount of LSCN loading is in the range of 45-55 wt% with an activation energy near 1.32 eV for oxygen reduction.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical performance of solution impregnated La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Ni0.2O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At temperatures between 600 and 750 degrees C, the polarization resistance of the 55 wt% LSCN loaded LSCN + GDC cathode is in the range of 1.07 and 0.08 Omega cm(2), which is only about one half of that for the conventional cathode.
Titulo: Enhanced electrochemical performance of solution impregnated La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Ni0.2O3-δ cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
